The paper discusses the use of prior knowledge in neural networks, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV). The specific example used in the paper is X-ray material decomposition, which falls under the category of image processing and analysis, and could also be classified under artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the potential for improved error estimation and network understanding, which could fall under neural networks (cs.NE) and information theory (cs.IT).
